<p><b>Shimon Even</b> (<a href="/wiki/Hebrew_language" title="Hebrew language">Hebrew</a>: <span lang="he" dir="rtl" xml:lang="he">שמעון אבן</span>‎; June 15, 1935 – May 1, 2004) was an <a href="/wiki/Israel" title="Israel">Israeli</a> <a href="/wiki/Computer_science" title="Computer science">computer science</a> researcher. His main topics of interest included <a href="/wiki/Algorithm" title="Algorithm">algorithms</a>, <a href="/wiki/Graph_theory" title="Graph theory">graph theory</a> and <a href="/wiki/Cryptography" title="Cryptography">cryptography</a>. He was a member of the Computer Science Department at the <a href="/wiki/Technion" title="Technion" class="mw-redirect">Technion</a> since 1974. Shimon Even was the PhD advisor of <a href="/wiki/Oded_Goldreich" title="Oded Goldreich">Oded Goldreich</a>, a prominent cryptographer.</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Books">Books</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Shimon_Even&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Books">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li><i>Algorithmic Combinatorics</i>, Macmillan, 1973.</li>
<li><i>Graph Algorithms</i>, Computer Science Press, 1979. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0716780445" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0-7167-8044-5</a>.</li>
</ul>
